    {
      "number": 2,
      "title": "「了」的用法小结(2) — Summary of le Part 2",
      "explanation": "了(le) has two main uses: (1) After a verb — marks a completed action: 我(wǒ)吃(chī)了(le)。(I ate / have eaten.) (2) At the end of a sentence — marks a change of state or new situation: 天黑了(It's gotten dark)。(It has gotten dark.) These two uses can also combine: 他(tā)走(zǒu)了(le)。(He has left — both completed action and new situation). Learning to identify which use applies is key.",
      "examples": [
        {
          "chinese": "我买了一件礼物，送给她了。",
          "pinyin": "Wǒ mǎi le yí jiàn lǐ wù, sòng gěi tā le.",
          "english": "I bought a gift and gave it to her (completed actions)."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "新年到了，大家都很高兴。",
          "pinyin": "Xīn nián dào le, dà jiā dōu hěn gāo xìng.",
          "english": "The New Year has arrived (change of state); everyone is very happy."
        }
      ],
