    {
      "number": 3,
      "title": "能愿动词「得」— Modal Verb dei (must / have to)",
      "explanation": "得(děi) is a modal verb meaning 'must' or 'have to'. It expresses obligation or necessity. Formula: Subject + 得(děi) + Verb. Negation: 不用(bú yòng, don't need to) or 不能(bù néng, cannot) — NOT 不得(which has a different meaning). Example: 你(nǐ)得(děi)多(duō)休息(xiū xi)。(You must rest more.) 我(wǒ)今天(jīn tiān)得(děi)回家(huí jiā)。(I have to go home today.)",
      "examples": [
        {
          "chinese": "明年你得再来一次！",
          "pinyin": "Míng nián nǐ děi zài lái yí cì!",
          "english": "Next year you must come again!"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "今天是节日，我得送她礼物。",
          "pinyin": "Jīn tiān shì jié rì, wǒ děi sòng tā lǐ wù.",
          "english": "Today is a holiday; I have to give her a gift."
        }
      ],
